If I want to create an ann account in my Linux host, I run two commands:

sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash -G sudo ann
sudo passwd ann

After I have the ann account created, I can install heroku into the ann account:

ssh -AY ann@localhost
cd ~
wget https://cli-assets.heroku.com/heroku-cli/channels/stable/heroku-cli-linux-x64.tar.gz -O heroku.tar.gz
tar -xvzf heroku.tar.gz
ln -s heroku-cli*linux-x64 heroku

echo 'export PATH=${HOME}/heroku/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
bash
heroku auth:login
heroku status
